Disk Resize Solution:

Increased the volume on AWS.
Noted that increasing the volume (e.g., from 8 GiB to 30 GiB) does not automatically expand the filesystem inside the instance.
Steps to fix the issue:
Use cloud-utils to grow the partition (sudo growpart /dev/xvda 1).
Resize the filesystem with resize2fs to utilize the newly allocated space.
